article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 82, Texas Wesleyan 73
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas (AP) -- Marcus Clark scored 18 points and had seven assists to lead Stephen F. Austin to an 82-73 victory over Texas Wesleyan on Tuesday night. Clark also made all four of his 3-point attempts and hit both his free throws for Stephen F. Austin (2-0). Josh Alexander scored 15 points and Antuane Miller added 14. Anthony Paez had a game-high 10 rebounds and six assists. The Lumberjacks led 47-32 at halftime. Khayri McKinney led Texas Wesleyan (2-3) with a game-high 21 points and made all six of his free throw attempts. Brad Schilder added 16 points and shot 3-of-4 from 3-point range. Scott Reasoner scored 11 points and Nino Etienee added 10 for Texas Wesleyan. Stephen F. Austin shot 48 percent from the field and Texas Wesleyan shot 48 percent.
